Courier Feedback

What do these shipment tracking terms mean?

EDD (Estimated Date of Delivery)

You can expect the order Delivery to your address on this date

Consignment Manifested

Your order has been accepted by the seller and is ready to be Picked Up by Courier

Order Picked

Your Order has been Picked from the Seller Warehouse

In-Transit

Your order has left the Courier Warehouse and is on its way to the destination location

Out for Delivery

Your order has left the Courier Warehouse in the destination city and is on the way to the destination address

RTO

Your order could not be delivered, and is in transit back to the seller warehouse
